#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.h1:17-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\events.htm+html.body.h1:17-1"
msgid "Frame Events"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:18-1
msgid ""
"JAWS makes extensive use of events within Windows and your applications to "
"determine when certain responses or actions are necessary. Events occur all "
"the time: when you press a key on your keyboard (KeyPressedEvent), when you "
"open a file containing text (NewTextEvent), when you TAB from one control to "
"another (FocusChangeEvent). Recognizing events in such a way that actions "
"can be taken allows JAWS to quickly and naturally respond appropriately as "
"you work."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:19-1
msgid ""
"Within frames, only specific events are used. You specify which events each "
"frame recognizes. When one of the events specified for a frame occurs, the "
"action you have associated with that event is taken."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:20-1
msgid "There are several parts to every event used with frames."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:22-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Frame Event Types</b>: There are four types "
"of frame events: On Focus, On Frame Key, On Play Action, and On Text. The "
"event type determines what causes actions within your frame to take place. "
"For example, if you want some specific action to take place whenever you "
"<b>TAB</b> to a control within the borders of a frame, assign an On Focus "
"event and associate the action to take place."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:23-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Event Actions</b>: Event actions are the "
"actions that occur when the event takes place. Each event you add activates "
"only one action. If you want to have several things occur when focus moves "
"into the borders of a frame, add the On Focus frame event several times, "
"assigning different actions to each instance of the event."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:24-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Action Attributes</b>: Many, but not all, "
"event actions require that you specify an attribute of some sort. For "
"example, if you set a frame to speak the contents of a window when some "
"event occurs, when you assign the Say Window action to the frame event, you "
"are prompted to specify which window is to be spoken."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:26-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\events.htm+html.body.p:26-1"
msgid "Frame Event Types"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:27-1
