msgid "Event Actions"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:30-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\events.htm+html.body.h2:30-1"
msgid "Frame Event Types"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:31-1
msgid "The following events are available for use with frames."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:32-1
msgid "On Focus"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:33-1
msgid ""
"This event occurs whenever the system focus moves into the borders of a "
"frame. If you want something to happen whenever you <b>TAB</b> to a specific "
"control in a dialog, create a frame at the location of the control, assign "
"the On Focus event, and add the actions you want to take place."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:34-1
msgid "On Frame Key"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:35-1
msgid ""
"This event occurs when the keyboard combination assigned to the frame is "
"pressed. The keyboard assignment is made within the General page of the "
"Frame Properties dialog."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:36-1
msgid "On Play Action"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:37-1
msgid ""
"This event occurs when the action, Play Frame Actions is used from another "
"frame and uses this frame as the attribute."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:38-1
msgid ""
"For example, assume you want several actions to take place in FrameA, but "
"only when an event occurs in FrameB. In FrameA, set up an On Play Action "
"event for each action you want to take place. Then in FrameB, set up the "
"event you want to use to initiate the actions. Assign the action, Play Frame "
"Actions to this event, and set FrameA as the attribute."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:39-1
msgid ""
"With the On Play Action event, you can specify the scope of the event to "
"determine when the event is recognized."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:40-1
msgid "On Text"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:41-1
msgid ""
"This event occurs when text is newly displayed within the borders of the "
"frame. Newly displayed text can be text typed into an edit field, or static "
"text in a dialog when the dialog first appears on the screen."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:42-1
msgid ""
"This text can be filtered so only specific text, or text with certain "
"attributes or colors activates the event."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:43-1
msgid ""
"For example, if you set the On Text event for a frame containing a list box, "
"and set the filter to recognize any highlighted text, every time you arrow "
"to a new item in the list box, newly highlighted text is displayed and the "
"event occurs, so the associated action takes place."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:44-1
msgid ""
"With the On Text event, you can specify the scope of the event to determine "
"when the event is recognized."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:45-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\events.htm+html.body.h2:45-1"
msgid "Text Filters"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:46-1
msgid ""
"When using the On Text event, you can specify that the event is recognized "
"only if the text newly written within the borders of the frame matches a "
"\"filter\" you set. This filter allows you to specify:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:48-1
msgid "Foreground (Text) Color"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:49-1
msgid "Background Color"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:50-1
msgid "Text attributes (Bold, Highlight, Italic, Underline, etc.)"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:51-1
msgid "A String of Text"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:53-1
msgid ""
"Foreground and background colors can be specified based on the text colors "
"at the location of the JAWS cursor (where it was before Frame Viewer was "
"started), by selecting the color names from the edit combo boxes, or by "
"typing in the RGB (Red, Green, Blue) numeric values."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:54-1
msgid ""
"When you specify a string of text for the filter, for the text in the frame "
"to be considered a match, it must be displayed all on one line, and it "
"cannot be interrupted by other text, symbols, or graphics."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:55-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\events.htm+html.body.h2:55-1"
msgid "Event Scope"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:56-1
msgid ""
"The On Play Action event and the On Text event can be set so these events "
"are only recognized under certain conditions. This allows you to limit when "
"the actions associated with these events occur."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:57-1
msgid "Set these Events to be recognized:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:59-1
msgid "All the time, regardless of the location of the system focus"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:60-1
msgid "Only when the system focus is within the frame"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:61-1
msgid "Only when the system focus is not within the frame"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:63-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\events.htm+html.body.h2:63-1"
msgid "Event Actions"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:64-1
msgid ""
"Actions are what make frames so powerful. Set actions to read the frame or "
"window, play a sound file, reposition cursors, or run a JAWS script. Each "
"event you add to your frame is associated with one action, but you can have "
"several instances of the same event type with different actions associated "
"with each, so when the event occurs, all the actions take place."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:65-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note</b>: Actions take place in the order "
"the associated event types are listed in the Events page of the Frame "
"Properties dialog."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:66-1
msgid ""
"When you add an event and choose an action to assign to it, as you move "
"through the list of actions, a description of each action is provided. Below "
"are summarized the types of actions that are available."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:67-1
msgid "Speak or Braille Information"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:68-1
msgid ""
"There are actions to speak or Braille the following types of information:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:70-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Text within a frame or window</b>: You "
"specify which frame or window."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:71-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Text with specific attributes in a frame or "
"window</b>: Specify the frame or window, and specify the attributes or "
"colors of the text."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:72-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">A string of text</b>: Just specify what you "
"want spoken or displayed in Braille."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:73-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">A structured message</b>: Specify a "
"combination of specific text and information gathered through use of script "
"functions."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:75-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note</b>: The actions related to Braille "
"only work while you are in structured mode."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:76-1
msgid "Move Cursors"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:77-1
msgid "There are actions to move cursors as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:79-1
msgid "Move the JAWS cursor to the top left corner of a frame"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:80-1
msgid "Move the JAWS cursor to the top left corner of a window"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:81-1
msgid "Move the JAWS cursor to the PC cursor"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:83-1
msgid "Play Sounds"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:84-1
msgid ""
"There are actions to play sounds you specify, system sounds, or to produce a "
"beep from the system speaker."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.h3:85-1
msgid "Other"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:86-1
msgid "There are also actions to:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:88-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Load JAWS Configuration Files</b>: Specify "
"the configuration files you wish to use."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:89-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Play Actions Specified in other Frames</b>: "
"An event occurring in one frame can be set to cause actions in another frame "
"to take place."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:90-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Run JAWS Scripts</b>: Enhance your frames "
"even further by using them together with JAWS scripts."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cevents.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:91-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Suppress Script Events</b>: Prevent script "
"events from causing information to be spoken or Brailed so as to avoid "
"duplicating the information your frame is providing."
msgstr ""

